  "body": "As a user\r\nI want to have my wallet synced across accounts\r\nSo that I don't have to create the same twice\r\n\r\n### Description\r\n\r\nIf a user creates/imports a wallet on an account, it should appear on any synced devices.\r\nSimilarly if any information is edited/changed/deleted, it should reflect on the synced devices.\r\n\r\n### Technical implementation\r\n\r\nWe should start from generated wallet, and on the other device they should appear as watch only addresses, no private key should be passed on the wire.\r\n\r\nThis is the first step, as there's some complications with generating the wallet on the other side, as it requires the user password.\r\n\r\nThe next step will be to mark those wallets as \"generate on the fly\", so that when the user inputs their password (either at login or when transacting), they should be generated, becoming the same as all generated wallets.",
